==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rhinoscleroma
<hw>Rhi`no*scle*ro"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Rhino-</ets> + <ets>scleroma</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A rare disease of the skin, characterized by the development of
very hard, more or less flattened, prominences, appearing first upon the
nose and subsequently upon the neighboring parts, esp. the lips, palate,
and throat.</def> <rj><au>J. V. Shoemaker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rhinoscope</ent>⟦br⟧
